TopicTitle: My "unmodded" install has 11,000 more patches than my modded install, what do I do?

Articles.Content:
I don't know what that means.

You may need to define "patch" in this context, and why it's bad.
as in module manager patches, with 38 mods...

Obviously 'unmodded' here does not actually mean without mods, so you'll need to specify more clearly what each of those installs really is. Start with posting a screenshot of the two GameData folders, or an actual list of the mods in either one. People can't simply guess at what you have installed.

Also, time to move this to the Tech Support (modded) section of the forum.

Ah. I see. You're making a joke.

I have 3 main installs. "Actual" where I have my mods. "Stockish" where I only have mods that don't introduce parts, and "unmodded" which only has a few mods. So I get where you're coming from.

56 minutes ago, Kaizen said:

:/

If that is/was your Gamedata folder, you have a problem.

 

Anyway, I guess there's no real question or support request here. Moving along.
A mod list would probably help.
